OL,3,CStudents taking legal action against
OL,4,Cuni for suspending black history course
OL,6,FIn alinked case, the Black Equity
OL,7,FOrganisation (BEO) is also bringing
OL,8,Flegal action and has issued a judicial
OL,9,Freview of the university's actions.
OL,11,FKehinde Adeogun director of legal
OL,12,Fservices at BEO, said: "Suspending the
OL,13,Fcourse without consultation when the
OL,14,Fissues are still prevalent, decreases
OL,15,Fthe opportunity for change, the aim of
OL,16,Fwhich is to see the effective
OL,17,Finclusion of black history into the
OL,18,Fcurriculum that is taught and studied
OL,19,Fin UK schools, especially in the
OL,20,Fcontext of key debates around
OL,21,Fdecolonising the curriculum."
